        "description": "[Green tea](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Green_tea#Chinese_green_tea) is one of the original teas in China, dating back to the Han Dynasty. It is prepared (steamed or pan-fried) soon after harvesting and before fermentation (oxidation) takes place and is lightly caffeinated. Green tea is the most widely produced tea in China, with many varieties, such as Dragon Well, Biluochun, and Gunpowder.\n\n**Characters**\n\n{綠} is *green*, and and {茶} is [tea](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tea), so {綠茶} is *green tea*.",
