        "description": "[Gunpowder tea](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gunpowder_tea) is a tea, usually green or oolong, that is prepared by rolling the leaves into small pellets. The English name *gunpowder* might be based on the round shape, or the smoky flavor, or the Mandarin pronunciation of 剛泡的 (gāng pào de), which means fresh brewed*.\n\n**Characters**\n\n[珠](https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/%E7%8F%A0) means *bead* or *pearl*, and {茶} is [tea](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tea), so this is sometimes called *pearl tea* (not to be confused with boba tea!)",
